    "Sugawara et al. (2022) observed that the diversity of contexts in MC questions determines the diversity of questions possible conditioned on the contexts.",
    "In their work they found that variables such as passage source, length, or readability measures do not significantly affect the model performance.",
    "Further, Khashabi et al. (2018) introduced the role of the original source from which the contexts are extracted in shaping overall complexity.",
    "Through the augmentation of the dataset by diversifying the corpus sources, they aimed to enhance the dataset quality.",
    "Question complexity has repeatedly been discussed within prior literature, with varying defi-nitions."
